OBSOLESCENT. Becoming obsolete;

going out of use; not entirely disused, but
gradually becoming so.

OBSTANTE. Withstanding;
See NON OBSTANTE.


hindering.

OBSTANTE. Withstanding;
See Non OBSTANTE.


hindering.

OFFICINA JUSTITIAE. The workshop
or office of justice. The chancery was formerly so called. See 8 Bl. Comm. 273;
Yates v. People, 6 Johns. (N. Y.) 363.

OVERLIVE. To survive; to live longer
than another. Finch, Law, b. 1, c. 3, no. 38;
1 Leon. 1. *

OVERPLUS. What is left beyond a certain amount; the residue; the remainder of
a thing. Lyon v. Tomkies, 1 Mees. & W. 603;
Page v. Leapingwell, 18 Ves. 460.
